article.description: Case Cookus threw seven touchdowns as Northern Arizona picked up its first season win, beating Division II New Mexico Highlands 73-3 on Saturday.
article.headline: Northern Arizona beats Div. II New Mexico Highlands 73-3
article.linkText: Northern Arizona beats Div. II New Mexico Highlands 73-3
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Case Cookus threw seven touchdowns as Northern Arizona picked up its first season win, beating Division II New Mexico Highlands 73-3 on Saturday. Cookus was 14-of-25 passing for 296 yards for the Lumberjacks (1-2). Emmanuel Butler was his primary target, picking up 99 yards and five scores on five receptions. Elijah Marks had 143 yards and two scores receiving. Freshman Joe Logan -- in his first career start -- ran for 172 yards and a pair of touchdowns, helping the Lumberjacks to amass 686 total yards. Cookus threw four touchdowns in the first quarter and another two in the second for a 49-3 lead at the break. New Mexico Highlands' only score came on a 25-yard field goal by Luke Jones with 7:48 to go in the first half. Cody Keith threw for 212 yards for the Cowboys.
